HEADWORD: organzine
<hw>or"gan*zine</hw> <pr>(⟦ocir⟧r"g⟦ait⟧n*z⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>organsin</ets>; cf. Sp. <ets>organsino</ets>, It.
<ets>organzino</ets>.]</ety> <def>A kind of double thrown silk of very
fine texture, that is, silk twisted like a rope with different strands,
so as to increase its strength.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

